==English==
===Etymology===
From Hindustani [[हिन्दुस्तानी]] / {{URchar|[[ہندوستانی]]}} (hindustānī) < Persian {{FAchar|[[هند]]}} ('''hend''' = ''Hindu'' +  {{FAchar|[[ستان]]}} ('''stan''' = ''land'') (''land of the Hindus'') + adjective suffix {{FAchar|[[ی]]}}.

===Adjective===
'''Hindustani'''
# Related to [[India]], or historically the entire Indian [[subcontinent]].
====Translations====
{{top}}
*Hindi: [[हिन्दुस्तानी]] (hindustānī)
{{mid}}
*Urdu: {{URchar|[[ہندوستانی]]}}
{{bottom}}
===Noun===
'''Hindustani''' ({{p}}: '''Hindustanis''')
# A [[person]] from India (historically the entire Indian subcontinent)
# An [[informal]] (colloquial) [[language]] made by blending of [[Hindi]] and [[Urdu]] languages.
